    "description": "<p style=\"\">  \t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">Welcome to this course on Accounting Inventory Valuation.</span>  </p>  <p style=\"\">  \t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">Every business involved in manufacture / trade of products will carry some inventories regularly. </span>  \t</p>  \t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">Inventory may be in the form of goods held for sale in the ordinary course of Business;</span>  \t\t</p>  \t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">Inventory may be in the process of production for such sale, or</span>  \t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">It may be in the form or materials or supplies to be consumed in the production process or in the rending of services. </span>  \t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">It becomes essential to value to these inventories to know </span>  \t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">a) Income earned;</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">b) Financial Position;</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">c) Liquidity Position;</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">d) Compliance with statutory requirements.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">Then a question would arise, How to Value the Inventory? Should it be valued at Cost or Market Price or Net Realisable Value? To answer all these, Knowledge on Inventory Valuation is essential for Entrepreneurs, Accountants / Finance Managers, Auditors, etc.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">Inventory Valuation plays significant role in presenting Financial Statements in a True and Fair Form.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">By taking this course, you will be learning</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">a) What is Inventory?</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">b) Significance of Inventory Valuation.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">c) Measurement / Valuation of Inventory.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">d) Cost of Inventory</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">e) Cost of Purchase</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">f) Cost of Conversion</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">g) Net Realisable Value</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">h) Techniques for Inventory Valuation</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">I) Specific Identification of Cost</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">j) First In First Out Method of Inventory Valuation</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">k) Last In First Out Method of Inventory Valuation</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">l) Simple Average Price Method</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">m) Weighted Average Price Method</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">n) Retail Method or Adjusted Selling Price Method.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">This course is structured in self learning pace style.</span>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</p>  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style=\"\">  \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span style=\"color: rgb(53, 53, 53);\">This course has video lectures explaining ea